Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 16:52:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 7/7] Loosen sample_trend_strategy EMA condition from
 crosses_above to state check

Confidence scoring's strategy_match component was permanently stuck at its
unmatched floor because sample_trend_strategy required EMA_9 crosses_above
EMA_20 (the exact one-bar transition) at the same instant market_regime ==
TRENDING_BULLISH. RegimeEngine's TRENDING_BULLISH classification itself
requires EMA_9 > EMA_20 > EMA_50 to already hold, so by the time regime
confirms a trend, the crossover has almost always already happened on an
earlier bar - the two conditions rarely coincide. Changed the condition to
EMA_9 > EMA_20 (a sustained-state check consistent with standard trend-
following entries) so it's satisfied whenever regime is already trending,
rather than only in the single bar the crossover occurs.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_017msKRAooRgtKyX1A2RMaxv
---
 spv-quantum-ai/config/strategies/sample_trend_strategy.yaml | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/spv-quantum-ai/config/strategies/sample_trend_strategy.yaml b/spv-quantum-ai/config/strategies/sample_trend_strategy.yaml
index 7fb1046..45d2073 100644
--- a/spv-quantum-ai/config/strategies/sample_trend_strategy.yaml
+++ b/spv-quantum-ai/config/strategies/sample_trend_strategy.yaml
@@ -9,7 +9,7 @@ name: sample_trend_strategy
 rules:
   conditions:
   - key: EMA_9
-    operator: crosses_above
+    operator: '>'
     source: indicator
     target: EMA_20
   - key: RSI
